From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
Date: Thu, 17 Oct 2019 11:40:34 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Fix MMC numbering via DT aliases for Iris Hub V2
Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [Iris Hub V2 specific]

The Iris Hub V2 requires the eMMC to be mmcblk0 and SD card to be mmcblk1
for the U-Boot/kernel partition layout to work correctly.

In kernel 6.6, the MMC subsystem respects DT aliases for device numbering.
Use /aliases node to explicitly assign mmc0 = eMMC (mmc2) and mmc1 = SD
(mmc1), matching the expected boot layout.

This replaces the old approach of patching drivers/mmc/core/block.c which
was fragile across kernel versions.

NOTE: This patch may need manual adjustment based on the actual
v6.6/standard/beaglebone kernel tree DTS content. The aliases node
may already exist and just need mmc0/mmc1 entries added, or the
existing entries may need to be changed.

---
 arch/arm/boot/dts/ti/omap/am335x-bone-common.dtsi | 5 +++++
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+)

diff --git a/arch/arm/boot/dts/ti/omap/am335x-bone-common.dtsi b/arch/arm/boot/dts/ti/omap/am335x-bone-common.dtsi
index 222222222222..333333333333 100644
--- a/arch/arm/boot/dts/ti/omap/am335x-bone-common.dtsi
+++ b/arch/arm/boot/dts/ti/omap/am335x-bone-common.dtsi
@@ -8,6 +8,11 @@

 / {
+	aliases {
+		mmc0 = &mmc2;	/* eMMC = mmcblk0 */
+		mmc1 = &mmc1;	/* SD card = mmcblk1 */
+	};
+
 	cpus {
 		cpu@0 {
 			cpu0-supply = <&dcdc2_reg>;
--
2.17.1
